article.headline: Louisiana Tech hits six FTs after SMU closes gap
article.linkText: Free throws down the stretch save No. 15 Louisiana Tech
article.story:
DALLAS -- Trina Frierson scored 21 points and grabbed 12
rebounds and Louisiana Tech (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today; No. 14 Associated Press) hit six free throws in the
closing seconds to hang on for a 74-64 victory over Southern
Methodist on Saturday night in the Western Athletic Conference
opener for both teams.

	   Louisiana Tech (8-2) led 66-61 with 1:32 remaining when
SMU's Shanta Ramdhanny was fouled on a 3-point shot.

	   Ramdhanny made all three free throws to cut the deficit to
66-64, but SMU (6-5) missed its next three shots.

	   Cheryl Ford put the Lady Techsters up 68-64 with a baseline
jumper, then Tech hit six consecutive free throws over the final 42
seconds. Ford finished with 16 points and 19 rebounds.

	   Andrea Cossey led SMU with 17 points, nine rebounds and three
steals. Ramdhanny scored 10 points, and Kaci Alexander added nine
points and eight rebounds.

	   Erica Smith scored 17 for Tech, and Amber Obaze 11 points and
five assists.
